George Winfred BENNINGFIELD v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6227. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. June 3, 1960. Donald G. Brotzman, U. S. Atty., and Robert S. Wham, Asst. U. S. Atty., Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
